it.cnr.isti.thematrix.scripting.sys

Class Symbol<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.cnr.isti.thematrix.scripting.sys.Symbol<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Literal, SymbolMissing

    public class Symbol<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    A Symbol represents an attribute of a dataset or a variable of the script. A Symbol has a name, a type and a value of the given type. It is a simple JavaBean for the fields value, name and type. Types are represented by values of the enum type DataType
    Author:
    edoardovacchi
